CREDIT SCORE CLASSIFICATION

We will be building a model to classify a customer as either "GOOD", "STANDARD", or "POOR" based on their credit score.

The original dataset can be found here.

In [19]:
# Define feature columns (X) and target variable (y)
X = df.drop(columns=['Credit_Score'])  # Features
y = df['Credit_Score']  # Target variable

# Split the data into a 70% training set and a 30% testing set while stratifying by 'Credit_Score'
X_train_1, X_test, y_train_1, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42, stratify=y)

# Instantiate the SMOTE object
smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)

# Fit and apply SMOTE to the training data
X_train, y_train = smote.fit_resample(X_train_1, y_train_1)

# Print the shapes of the resulting sets
print("X_train shape:", X_train.shape)
print("X_test shape:", X_test.shape)
print("y_train shape:", y_train.shape)
print("y_test shape:", y_test.shape)

X_train shape: (111666, 41)
X_test shape: (30000, 41)
y_train shape: (111666,)
y_test shape: (30000,)
In [20]:
# Create a StandardScaler instance
scaler = StandardScaler()

# Fit the scaler on the training data and transform both training and testing data
X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)

# Create and train the Logistic Regression model using scaled features
logistic_regression_model = LogisticRegression(random_state=42, max_iter=500)
logistic_regression_model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)

# Make predictions on the scaled test data
y_pred = logistic_regression_model.predict(X_test_scaled)

# Create a confusion matrix
confusion_mat = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)

# Plot the confusion matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.heatmap(confusion_mat, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="Blues", square=True)
plt.xlabel("Predicted")
plt.ylabel("Actual")
plt.title("Confusion Matrix")
plt.show()

# Print classification report
classification_rep = classification_report(y_test, y_pred)
print("Classification Report:\n", classification_rep)

# Print accuracy score
accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

print(f"Rounded Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred):.2f}")

In [23]:
# Create a label encoder instance
label_encoder = LabelEncoder()

# Encode the string labels during model training
y_train_encoded = label_encoder.fit_transform(y_train)

# Encode the string labels for the test set
y_test_encoded = label_encoder.transform(y_test)

# Create a simple neural network model
model = keras.Sequential([
    keras.layers.Input(shape=(X_train_scaled.shape[1],)),  # Input layer
    keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),  # Hidden layer with 64 units and ReLU activation
    keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),  # Hidden layer with 64 units and ReLU activation
    keras.layers.Dense(3, activation='softmax')  # Output layer with 3 units and softmax activation
])

# Compile the model
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history = model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_encoded, epochs=30, batch_size=32, validation_split=0.2, verbose=1)

# Make predictions on the scaled test data
y_pred_nn_encoded = model.predict(X_test_scaled)
y_pred_nn_encoded = y_pred_nn_encoded.argmax(axis=1)  # Convert softmax probabilities to class labels

# For evaluation, use the label encoder to decode the predictions
y_pred_nn_original = label_encoder.inverse_transform(y_pred_nn_encoded)

# Create a confusion matrix
confusion_mat_nn = confusion_matrix(y_test_encoded, y_pred_nn_encoded)

# Plot the confusion matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.heatmap(confusion_mat_nn, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="Blues", square=True)
plt.xlabel("Predicted")
plt.ylabel("Actual")
plt.title("Neural Network Confusion Matrix")
plt.show()

# Print classification report
classification_rep_nn = classification_report(y_test_encoded, y_pred_nn_encoded, target_names=label_encoder.classes_)
print("Neural Network Classification Report:\n", classification_rep_nn)

# Calculate and print the accuracy score
accuracy_nn = accuracy_score(y_test_encoded, y_pred_nn_encoded)
print("Neural Network Accuracy:", accuracy_nn)

X_train_o, X_test_o, y_train_o, y_test_o = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42, stratify=y)

# Create a StandardScaler instance
scaler = StandardScaler()

# Fit the scaler on the training data and transform both training and testing data
X_train_o_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_o)
X_test_o_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_o)

# Create a label encoder instance
label_encoder = LabelEncoder()

# Encode the string labels during model training
y_train_o_encoded = label_encoder.fit_transform(y_train_o)

# Encode the string labels for the test set
y_test_o_encoded = label_encoder.transform(y_test_o)

# Create and train a Random Forest Classifier
rf_model = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)
rf_model.fit(X_train_o_scaled, y_train_o_encoded)

# Make predictions on the scaled test data
y_pred_rf_encoded = rf_model.predict(X_test_o_scaled)

# For evaluation, use the label encoder to decode the predictions
y_pred_rf_original = label_encoder.inverse_transform(y_pred_rf_encoded)

# Create a confusion matrix
confusion_mat_rf = confusion_matrix(y_test_o_encoded, y_pred_rf_encoded)

# Plot the confusion matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.heatmap(confusion_mat_rf, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="Blues", square=True)
plt.xlabel("Predicted")
plt.ylabel("Actual")
plt.title("Random Forest Confusion Matrix")
plt.show()

# Print classification report
classification_rep_rf = classification_report(y_test_o_encoded, y_pred_rf_encoded, target_names=label_encoder.classes_)
print("Random Forest Classification Report:\n", classification_rep_rf)

# Calculate and print the accuracy score
rounded_accuracy_rf = round(accuracy_rf, 2)
print("Random Forest Accuracy:", rounded_accuracy_rf)
